post_cb({"24836257": {"ParentId": "24836251", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>[class.ctor]/6</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_24836251_24836257_0\">... The implicitly-defined default constructor performs the set of initializations of the class that would be\n  performed by a user-written default constructor for that class with no <em>ctor-initializer</em> (12.6.2) and an empty\n  <em>compound-statement.</em> ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In other words, the constructor that the compiler generates is the same as</p>\n<pre><code>Test() {}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Since <code>a</code> is not explicitly initialized by the constructor, <code>a</code> is left uninitialized.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "481267", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "24836257", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2014-07-19T02:47:55.913", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-19T02:47:55.913"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_24836251_24836257_0": {"section_id": 370, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "length": 16}}, "n3337": {"so_24836251_24836257_0": {"section_id": 360, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "length": 16}}, "n4659": {"so_24836251_24836257_0": {"section_id": 384, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "length": 16}}}, "24836251": {"CommentCount": "6", "ViewCount": "50", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "868423", "CreationDate": "2014-07-19T02:45:17.580", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-19T02:54:59.643", "Title": "What is the behavior of the compiler's ctor?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "24836257", "LastEditDate": "2014-07-19T02:54:59.643", "Id": "24836251", "Score": "-3", "Body": "<p>If I define a class's ctor and dtor like so,</p>\n<pre><code>struct Test\n{\n    //Test(){}\n    //~Test(){}\n    int a;\n}\n\nint main()\n{\n    Test t;\n    std::cout &lt;&lt; t.a &lt;&lt; std::endl; \n    //^Prints garbage if ctor/dtor are defined, 0 if commented out.\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Why is <code>a</code> 0 in one case and garbage in the other?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "868423", "AnswerCount": "1"}});